column5: Just going to say,that rock sitting up,that water flow ,looks real good !
sweet. There is  a part inside us that such places speak to. Lowers the blood pressure, clears the mind.
If I could still walk ten miles, I';d be doing the same thing Bro. Great report my friend.

I was one that would go with the crowd many years ago.Shoulder to shoulder. It was so frustrating back then. Finding new waters and only sharing  with true friends,has come more enjoyable. I just wished,I had of done this many years ago.   I would of invited,but my CPR is expired. LOL    Funny you say that Dave. I sat there and had a bite to eat and a smoke. Left a fly dangling in the pool down stream.  Rick,it did.   Dan,the walk up river is a great work out. When I make my way back,oh,what a relief it is.
